CONTEXT CompositionISASiblings IN ENGLISH

PURPOSE CONTEXT CompositionISASiblings
{+ This test must fail because meet(A,B) does not exist.
   A and B are sibling types (both subtypes of C) with no ordering between them. +}

CLASSIFY A ISA C
CLASSIFY B ISA C

RELATION r[W*A]
RELATION s[B*Z]
RELATION result[W*Z]

RULE testCompositionISASibling: result = r;s

ENDCONTEXT
